column2: Data for the report: "PATTERNS AND PROJECTIONS OF HIGH TIDE FLOODING ALONG THE U.S. COASTLINE USING A COMMON IMPACT THRESHOLD"

Suggested Citation:  Sweet, W.V., G. Dusek, J. Obeysekera, J. Marra (2018). Patterns and Projections of High Tide Flooding Along the U.S. Coastline Using a Common Impact Threshold. NOAA Tech. Rep. NOS CO-OPS 86, 44p.
1) "NaN" implies that either the station was not yet in service or that less than 80% of the hourly data existed during a particular year (meteorological year: May - April)
2) Data metric provided (for historical observations and for 6 future scenarios) is days per year with an exceedance at or above the specified threshold
3) The scenarios assessed are the global rise scenarios of the U.S. Federal Interagency Sea Level Rise and Coastal Flood Hazard Task
Derived' (1.04*GT + 0.5 m) High Tide Flood Threshold
